{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Extend universal credit payments to cover 53 week rent years",
        "additional_details": "The 2024-25 financial year has 53 rent weeks and universal credit claimants will receive only 52 weeks' worth of housing costs. We think this may leave some people in arrears.",
        "background": "The Department for Work and Pensions calculates universal credit payments based on a 52-week year. Some years where there are 53 weeks, if you receive universal credit for housing, you may need to pay for the extra week of rent yourself. ",
